<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-456-820  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 456 820.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  August 1989 v14 n8 p84(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Let the Mac entertain you. (Software Review) (MacroMind Directorvideo-production software for Macintosh) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Baran, Nick.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MacroMind's $695 MacroMind Director lets any Macintosh userproduce elaborate video productions including full animation andsound.andP;  The program is an improved and enhanced version of thecompany's VideoWorks product, adding over 100 new features.andO;MacroMind Director includes a new color paint program, automaticanimation, new music and sound capabilities, MIDI support, and animproved user interface with on-line help.andP;  It contains two mainmodules: Overview, in which the user creates individual frames orvisual images, and Studio, which combines the images into a'movie' with appropriate timing.andP;  MacroMind Director runs on anyMac platform, but is best with the Mac II because the latter has256 colors.andP;  Full video-production capability requires alarge-screen display, a scanner, and digital-to-analog conversionequipment.andP;  MacroMind is a tool for the serious professionalrather than casual hobbyists.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (products)MacroMind Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs)MacroMind Director (Multimedia software).andO;Topic:     Computer graphicsEvaluationVideo RecordingsSoftware SelectionGraphics SoftwareSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>